E. COLI, STATE PRISONS - USA (CALIFORNIA)
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
Date: Sat, 1 Aug 1998 18:16:31 -0800
Source:
http://dailynews.yahoo.com/headlines/local/state/california/California
Headlines updated 6:22 PM ET Jul 31
Via: Philip Henika <zowie@telis.org>

E-coli Outbreak In State Prisons -
(SACRAMENTO) -- The State Department of Corrections is investigating an
outbreak of the deadly [_E. coli_ infection] at three prisons in Northern
California. There are six confirmed cases among inmates, with ten others
reporting symptoms consistent with the infection. Officials suspect tainted
milk and vegetables may be responsible.
--
ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[We presume these infections to be caused by enterohemorrhagic strains of
_E. coli_ (EHEC), but no further information is available to us at this
time. - Mod.ES]
